  "prompt": "Who is the best mobile in 2016?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" mobile phone in 2016 can vary based on individual preferences and needs, but several models stood out due to their performance, features, and popularity.\n\n1. **Samsung Galaxy S7/S7 Edge**: These phones were praised for their design, camera quality, and performance. The S7 Edge, in particular, had a striking curved display that attracted a lot of attention.\n\n2. **iPhone 7/7 Plus**: Apple's iPhone 7 series, released in September 2016, boasted improvements in camera technology, water resistance, and overall performance. The 7 Plus was especially noted for its dual-camera system.\n\n3. **Google Pixel/Pixel XL**: Introduced in October 2016, the Google Pixel series offered a clean Android experience, excellent performance, and impressive camera capabilities.\n\n4. **OnePlus 3/3T**: These phones were recognized for delivering high-end specs at a more affordable price compared to other flagship models. They featured strong performance, fast charging, and a sleek design.\n\n5. **LG G5**: Known for its modular design, the LG G5 allowed users to swap out different components, such as the battery and camera accessories, which set it apart in the market.\n\nUltimately, the best mobile phone of 2016 would depend on what features and qualities you value most, such as camera performance, battery life, software experience, or design.",
